$ python -m virtualenv enviro
$ source enviro/bin/activate							#Activates/enter virtual enviroment called enviro
(enviro)...$

-------------If the above dont work try installing-----------------
INSTALL pip
-----------
$ sudo apt-get install python-pip

INSATLL Virtualenv
------------------
$ sudo pip install virtualenv

NOW DO THE FOLLOWING
---------------------
$ mkdir ~/.virtualenvs

$ sudo pip install virtualenvwrapper

$ export WORKON_HOME=~/.virtualenvs
$ nano ~/.bashrc + Enter and then paste . /usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.shat the very end of the bashrc file

NOW
----
use: 'workon' to switch between virtual enviroments

